Boss tiers are a quick shorthand for how dangerous a boss fight is
expected to be.

Tier labels appear as:

  T1
  T2
  T3
  T4
  T5

As the tier rises, expect the fight to demand more from a player or
group. Higher tiers usually bring more punishment, more durability, and
more meaningful rewards.

A boss tier is not a promise that every class or every level range will
handle the fight the same way. It is a difficulty signal, not a perfect
matchmaking number.

In the Eternal Dungeon, leader encounters eventually grow into true boss
tiers as floors climb higher and higher.

